    "body": "This is not something that we are prioritizing internally at the moment. There are tradeoffs here as faster blocktimes result in the db growing larger over time resulting in slower i/o as well as overall performance issues in the node itself. The real solution here is to give better preconfirmations, ie the block builder optimistically returns the receipt as if the block has already been mined. This obviously introduces some amount of trust if there is not a cryptographic/economic scheme enforcing it.\r\n\r\nDo you think that supporting lower L2 blocktime is possible with a small diff? Do you think its possible without a hardfork? This is not a small task to take on as its very consensus critical",
